Hi! A link to your code would be greatly appreciated. Also what does doesn’t appear to work mean? Does it not drive around in field oriented swerve or are the inputs you’re getting from your gyro wacky? Hmm I’m not sure why it would only work at a 0 degree or 180 degree heading.

Here’s a link to my team’s REV swerve code. Our field oriented swerve code wasn’t working this week because our Navx was physically broken. I’d recommend logging your gyro output using Smart Dashboard through a line of code like this:

SmartDashboard.putNumber("GyroAngle", m_gyro.getAngle());

and using something like Advantage Scope to look at the logs.

If anything looks wrong (quick jumps or disconnects) in the graph you see, something is probably physically wrong with it. So far this season, all of our gyro problems have been physical from metal shavings or physically broken things.

Anyways, good luck and I hope you get it working! Let me know if you have any questions. I’m happy to help!
